Product Description

How To Use Grampa's Weeder. Please Read!

1) Center Tool Over Weed

Simply place the tool over the center of the invasive plant.

2) Press Into Ground

Press down on the footpad straight down into the ground then REMOVE YOUR FOOT.

3) Lean The Handle

This Is Where The Magic Happens!!

Lean the tool towards the footpad. Do not lift the tool or twist. Only when you lean the tool, will the forks pinch around the weed.

Grampa's Story

Grampa's Weeder has been pulling out weeds and their roots for over a hundred years! This ingeniously designed weed removal tool was invented in 1913 in Seattle, Washington and people living in the Great Northwest quickly made it the MUST-HAVE weed puller for getting rid of weeds quickly and easily. Production of the stand-up weeder stopped in 1941 so that all available metal could be put towards the war effort and unfortunately, once the war ended, manufacturing of this wonderful weed removal tool never resumed.

-

This all changed in 1999 when my husband Greg found my mother's strange looking garden tool in her garage. Once he figured out what it was and how it worked, he was hooked! The next thing we knew, Grampa's Gardenware Co. was born and we were hand-making this turn-of-the-century weed puller tool in that very same garage. We are thrilled to introduce Grampa's Weeder to gardeners everywhere. As a small family business, we've come a long way in 25 years. It's amazing that this century-old weed puller tool, a simple lever, remains one of the most effective weed & dandelion removers on the market. Not only does it eliminate the need for chemicals, but it also prevents strain on your knees and back. What worked well in 1913 still works well today. As the saying goes, "Everything Old Is New Again", and Grampa's Weeder proves it every day with its ingenious design that has stood the test of time.

Grampa's Weeder - The Original Stand Up Weed Puller Tool with Long Handle

Grampa's Weeder is the Original Stand-Up Weed Remover Tool

Don't be fooled by the look-alikes! Grampa's Weeder was conceived back in 1913 and its ingenious design works effectively over a century later. Lots of happy customers depend on Grampa's stand up weed puller tool to keep their gardens weed-free without harmful-toxic chemicals and weed killers.

Bamboo Long Handle and Powder Coated Metal Construction

Tackle the most persistent weeds in your garden without the aching back and dirty fingernails. All you need to do is Press down on the footpad straight down into the center of the weed then REMOVE YOUR FOOT. Then Lean the tool towards the footpad. Do not lift the tool or twist. Only when you lean the tool, will the forks pinch around the weed.

Simple Design That Works

The statement "They don't make things like they used to" is what Grampa's Weeder is all about. You can rely on this ingenious design to make removing dandelions & other weeds more manageable and enjoyable.

Grampa's Stand Up Weed Puller

How We Started

In 1999, my husband Greg found my mother's strange looking garden tool in her garage. Once he figured out what it was and how it worked, he was hooked! The next thing we knew, Grampa's Gardenware Co. was born and we were hand making this turn-of-the-century tool in that very same garage.

What Makes Our Products Unique

Grampa builds durable long lasting garden tools that are simple and easy to use. Grampa's Weeder allows you to effortlessly pull weeds standing up, which saves your back and knees. No harmful chemicals are needed. Been around for over 100 years.

Why We Love What We Do

We love seeing the look on people's faces when they use the tool for the first time and say, "Where has this been my whole life!?". Introducing Grampa to gardeners all across the world is one of the most rewarding feelings and we love showing everyone this ingenious old-fashioned tool from 1913.

American Family Owned Business

Our family is proud to continue Grampa's journey for generations to come!

Materials

  • Handle: The weeder boasts a long, resilient bamboo handle, renowned for its strength-to-weight ratio.
  • Head: Powder coated steel offers a high degree of durability and rust resistance.

Quality

  • Each weeder undergoes rigorous quality checks to ensure that the union between bamboo and steel is seamless, providing a reliable tool.
  • Product weight is 2.3 pounds

Capacity

  • Designed for a variety of common garden weeds, the tool works best at removing weeds in softer soil types.
  • The weeder excels in removing weeds with a tap root.

Limitations

  • While the tool is highly effective for most common weeds, it may struggle with particularly large or woody roots that exceed the grasp capacity of the steel claws.
  • For soils that are overly rocky or dense clay, additional effort may be required to penetrate and secure the weed for pulling.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

4.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and reliable weeder!
Reviewed in the United States on April 10, 2024
Style: ToolVerified Purchase
I have been in my house for almost 10-years and have inherited a yard full of deeply stubborn weeds. I have killed my back, hands, and neck trying to pull out several of them. Because they are deep rooted in my lawn, the use of weed killer sprays means sacrificing my lawn in the process...which isn't a choice for me. In all this time, I have had to just simply trim them down and keep up with, but never getting rid of them. However, that's now a thing of the past thanks to Grampa's Weeder! By stepping on a foot pedal, the claw grips the weed and removes it from the ground as you tilt the handle back. In seconds, these deeply infested rooted weeds were gone! It's almost like magic! I initially discovered this tool on TikTok and watched many video product reviews from people who used it. After months of watching, I decided to go ahead and purchase one and I am glad I did!

Pros:

- Reduces back strain: The long handle allows you to weed while standing upright, reducing strain on your back and knees.
- Easy to use: The simple design with a foot pedal makes Grampa's Weeder easy to operate for gardeners of all ages and abilities.
- Durable: Made with high-quality materials like steel and hardwood, Grampa's Weeder is built to last.
- Effective on many weeds: Grampa's Weeder works well on a variety of weeds, including dandelions and thistles.
- Eco-friendly: By removing weeds manually, you can avoid using harmful herbicides in your yard.

Cons:

-Limited use: Grampa's Weeder is a single-purpose tool and may not be effective for all types of weeds or gardens. For example, it might not be ideal for delicate plants or very rocky soil (or gardens where rock features are used.

- Clogging possible: The claw may clog with weeds or debris, requiring you to stop and clean it out.
Not for deep-rooted weeds: Grampa's Weeder may not be strong enough to remove weeds with very deep taproots, although for my yard this wasn't an issue. If the soil is very damp, the dirt tends to stick to the claw and get clogged requiring clean up, but this was a small price to pay for having the weed pulled out. Unclogging is very easy to resolve.

5.0 out of 5 stars Precise and complete weed extraction! Fantastic!
Reviewed in Canada on May 8, 2023
Style: ToolVerified Purchase
We have a massive weed problem this spring. I spent a few days using a Fiskar's puller and then a few days using this one. I far and away prefer Grampa's Weeder. It's lighter and more precise and the iron plucker is sturdy and pulls HUGE prickly weeds and dandelions and various assorted weeds out clean, even when they come with 10 inch roots. I have been so impressed with it. Only downside is that it doesn't have an ejector so you have to put a glove on one hand and pull the weed off the end each time. However, this also makes it much easier on the back, shoulders and arms, as I feel like the extractors on plastic weeders also takes more muscle/effort.

If you are older, have mobility issues or have an injury in the shoulder or arm - this is the one to go with, as it makes weeding your yard a more leisurely (and somehow satisfying) task. Because you can clearly see the claw, it's much easier to position it right over the centre of the weed and get a precise and perfect pull the first time, which I wasn't able to do a lot of times with the heavier plastic weeders. So happy I bought this as it's a total game-changer for my weeding and gardening. At first I wasn't sure something so light and simple would be effective but I was blown away at how well it works. Highly recommended! Also - best time to use weeders like this is just after it rains, or first thing in the morning when the soil is still damp and soft.
